    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-02-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="75"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <head>75. Central Intelligence Agency Information Report<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d75fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency Files, Job 79–00149A,
                            <gloss target="#t_DDOIMS_1">DDO/IMS</gloss> Files, African Division,
                        Senate Select Committee, Volume II, Box 23, Folder 1. Secret; Noforn;
                        Continued Control; Routine.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-02-15">February 15, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TDCS–3/465, 477, Field Report [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Congo Security Report on Death of <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1"
                            >Lumumba</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Two security officers who went Elisabethville 10–14 Feb for purpose
                    investigating death of <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Lumumba</persName> returned
                    Leopoldville 14 Feb and reported they had seen and identified body of <persName
                        corresp="#p_LPE_1">Lumumba</persName> and his two companions. Bodies were
                    rather badly mutilated and showed evidence of having been dead some time. They
                    could not determine from superficial examination exactly what was direct cause
                    death but they did not notice gun shot wounds.</p>
                <p>2. Security officers said no one believes legend of victims having been massacred
                    by villagers 12 February.</p>
                <p>3. Field dissem: <gloss target="#t_CINCLANT_1">CINCLANT</gloss>
                </p>
                <p>End of message.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
